e with their greater strategy: Over the past few
years, the company has mostly invested its marketing dollars in custom dres=
ses for the red carpet instead of echo-chamber runway shows.)=C2=A0

Was it worth it? I suspect that social media tracking firms will start spit=
ting out data on Inauguration Day brand chatter very soon, but here=E2=80=
=99s what we know now. While the brand=E2=80=99s Instagram account initiall=
y lost about 15,000 followers, they=E2=80=99ve already regained about 10,00=
0, and more importantly=E2=80=A6 they=E2=80=99ve sold dresses and coats. Fo=
r instance,
four people have already put down deposits for Ivanka Trump=E2=80=99s pearl=
-beaded gown, which she wore to parties on Sunday. (I don=E2=80=99t think t=
he company has determined the final retail price, but let=E2=80=99s just sa=
y that dresses of that ilk can be as much as $15,000=E2=80=94often a whole =
lot more.)=C2=A0

I rang up Oscar de la Renta C.E.O. Alex Bolen earlier today to ask him how =
