MDQ5NDc2fQ/c8324e1f93b29c0aacb410965c5fe3ed6c4ebb7ae5d13c67d5fb2c3847d10394=
" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">Lululemon=E2=80=99s AB=
C trouser</a>, were also well represented.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Perh=
aps I shouldn=E2=80=99t have been surprised. The 10-year-old San Diego bran=
d leaned into an upscale comfortable semi-aesthetic that metastasized durin=
g the pandemic=E2=80=94an era that took on a millennial-fabricated work-lif=
e balance fantasy wherein office workers could relocate to far-flung locale=
s and log into Zooms between beach runs and long hikes. (Sorry, kids, it do=
esn=E2=80=99t work that way in the real world.) Most brands in the space
enter the market at the performance tier, the top of the pyramid=E2=80=94Ho=
ka and On were discovered by hardcore runners before they became fashion sh=
oes; ditto Lululemon and Alo in the yoga space. Vuori, on the other hand, e=
ntered the zeitgeist via former lax bros who worked at hedge funds and prac=
tice mediation for career advancement.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-botto=
m:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Nevertheless, or=
 perhaps because of this market capture, the business began an
impressive ascent. As a pure-play direct-to-consumer business when that cha=
nnel seemed indomitable, Vuori attracted significant investor interest and =
made shrewd strategic investments in launching a women=E2=80=99s line, lean=
ing into wholesale, and building a brick-and-mortar retail business. In 202=
1, SoftBank made a Series B investment at a valuation of $4 billion. This p=
ast November, the company raised a Series C at $5.5 billion, with investmen=
ts from General Atlantic and Stripes.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">These days, it=E2=80=99s hard=
 to find a premium North American shopping destination without a Vuori or o=
ne coming soon. The brand claims to have a 50-50 sales split between the me=
n=E2=80=99s and women=E2=80=99s category, which is rare. (Lululemon famousl=
y had a difficult time establishing itself in the men=E2=80=99s category be=
cause its logo appeared too feminine. They had to work a testicular referen=
ce into the name of their ABC tech pants to make the yoga
brand safe for insecure dudes.) In the <em>Times</em> story, founder and C.=
E.O. <strong>Joe</strong> <strong>Kudla</strong> proudly touted the frugali=
ty he absorbed in his past life as a C.P.A., boasting that Vuori has <em>ne=
ver</em> acquired customers at a loss. Perhaps it=E2=80=99s a Vuori world a=
nd we=E2=80=99re just living in it=E2=80=A6</p></div>
